      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Skipping your basal insulin without professional guidance is dangerous because it often leads to dangerous blood sugar spikes rather than preventing hypoglycemia, especially given how basal rates are calculated. While it is logical to match carb intake to meal insulin, basal insulin is a background requirement for life that your body cannot leave without risking high blood sugar (hyperglycemia) during sleep. Since you are awake and aware, the smartest immediate step is to wait until morning and then contact your healthcare team to review your specific dose adjustment needs for tonight.",
